kanji.examples:
予期 (よき) expectation; assumption
学期 (がっき) school term; semester
定期 (ていき) fixed period; fixed term
延期 (えんき) postponement; deferment
時期 (じき) time; season
kanji.koohii1: The slowest remote chess game ever: a one month period between every move.
kanji.koohii2: The girl´s panties are all in the bushel basket as it´s that time of the month again... her period.

kanji_info.image_description: A surreal scene where a giant, fluffy meatball (representing "meat") sits on a calendar date, acting as a bizarre, fleshy bookmark.  The date is prominently displayed on the calendar page, emphasizing the "date" meaning.

kanji.meaning: not yet; still; sign of the ram
kanji.koohii1: I believe a better version of that by mameha1977: [Cheat] Remember these as a set: The tree (木) does not yet (未) have exremities (末) of vermilion (朱).
kanji.koohii2: [Cheat] Remember these as a set: The tree (木) is not yet (末) vermilion (朱).

kanji_info.image_description: A playful ram made entirely of wood, frolicking in a field of freshly sprouted wooden saplings. The ram is cheerfully bleating, signifying that it is not yet fully grown (not yet).

kanji.examples:
年末 (ねんまつ) end of the year
粗末 (そまつ) crude; rough; shabby
週末 (しゅうまつ) weekend
末（すえ） (すえ) tip; end
末（まつ） (まつ) the end of
kanji.koohii1: The tree has reached the extremity of its growth and no longer produces small/ new branches at the top. Instead the existing top branch just grows longer and longer.
kanji.koohii2: There are no great stories for this one yet/ and I always forget it.. So/ let´s try something ridiculous: The man lived by himself in the wilderness/ with no females within miles. So/ his only way of relief was to stick his extremity into a small hole in a tree.. The poor guy. Which horizontal stroke is the extremity? The longer one or the shorter one? That/ my friends/ is up to your own imaginations. I´d prefer not to dwell on that point/ myself. ;).

kanji_info.image_description: A whimsical forest where the trees have tiny houses at their very tips. These houses are intricately detailed and show signs of human life, representing the "end" or "tip" where life flourishes.

kanji.examples: 約束 (やくそく) promise; agreement
kanji.components: 木: tree; wood 口: mouth
kanji.koohii1: Mnemonic: Bundle of joy. Here I see the proverbial stork with a baby hanging from its mouth fly straight into a tree. Painful/ but he doesn´t drop the bundle.
kanji.koohii2: Unlike in 杏/ this big mouth isn´t content to wait for apricots to fall in his mouth/ so he has climbed the tree and is taking them in bundles.

kanji_info.image_description: A mischievous, smiling mouth made of wood is playfully trying to control a small forest of wooden trees, tying them together with vines and twigs. The scene depicts the "control" aspect of the kanji.

kanji.kun_reading: は・たす/は・て/は・てる
kanji.examples:
効果 (こうか) effect; efficacy
効果的 (こうかてき) effective; successful
結果 (けっか) result; consequence; outcome
果物 (くだもの) fruit
kanji.components: 田: rice field; rice paddy 木: tree; wood
kanji.koohii1: If only Eve had used her brains and not taken the forbidden fruit from the tree.
kanji.koohii2: Eve ate fruit from the tree and knowledge filled her brain.…

kanji_info.image_description: A bountiful harvest in a rice paddy where the rice stalks are laden with colorful, jewel-like fruits growing from wooden branches.  The fruits symbolize the completion and achievement represented by the kanji, with the rice paddy emphasizing the idea of a rich and abundant outcome.

short_text_with_quiz.text_english: I started a short-term part-time job this semester.  It's only for a short period, until the end of the school term. I'm looking forward to the results.  I hope it will be effective in helping me save money for the future.  I hope it won't cause inconvenience during my busy schedule.  I'm working during my free time, in the middle of my studies. I want to make the most of this short time period.

song.style: 1940s big band,  Lounge Singer,  male vocals

song_lyrics.lyrics_japanese:
短期の目標、長期の夢、
学期末、新たな期間が始まる。
未来を築き、効果的に明るく、
精一杯期待して頑張るよ。

週末の予定、たてたてで、
最中に心が揺らいだ。
万が一延期になっても、
乗り越えていく、きっと大丈夫。

この短期のプロジェクト、粗末だけど、
結果は最高になるはずさ。
長期的な計画は得意分野、
成功の末、見てみせるよ。

年末には、振り返って見るわ、
期待通りになったかどうか。
時期は今、季節はちょうどいい、
輝く未来に向かって頑張る。

この期間の末、新しい光がさす、
不便をかけるけど頑張るよ。
私の性格、強く、真実で、
営業時間中は、仕事に取り組む。
song_lyrics.lyrics_english_translation:
Short-term goals, long-term dreams,
The semester ends, a new period begins.
Building a future, effective and bright,
Hoping for the best, with all my might.

Weekend plans, hastily made,
In the middle of the week, my heart swayed.
In the unlikely event of a delay,
I'll overcome, come what may.

This short-term project, crudely done,
But the end result will be second to none.
Long-term planning is my forte,
The tip of success, I will see, and I will retort.

At the year's end, I'll reflect and see,
If my expectations have come to be.
The time is now, the season's right,
To work towards a future, shining bright.

The end of this period brings new light,
Despite any inconvenience, I will fight.
My personality, strong and true,
During business hours, my work I'll pursue.
song_lyrics.song_title: 学期末から始まる未来
